## OPA — Policy as Code

Open Policy Agent (OPA) externalizes authorization decisions from application code. Policies are written in Rego:

```rego
# policy.rego
package orders.authz

# Default: deny all
default allow = false

# Allow if user owns the order
allow {
    input.method == "GET"
    input.path = ["orders", order_id]
    order := data.orders[order_id]
    order.customer_id == input.user.id
}

# Allow admins full access
allow {
    input.user.roles[_] == "ADMIN"
}
```

```java
// Spring Boot: ask OPA before serving request
@PreAuthorize("@opaClient.isAllowed(#orderId, authentication)")
@GetMapping("/orders/{orderId}")
public Order getOrder(@PathVariable String orderId) { ... }
```

Benefits: policies are version-controlled, testable, auditable, and separate from application code.
